      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Yield force QoI comparison — Laboratory 2 (N=5)",
      "description": "FEA-predicted yield force compared against five physical F1717 specimens tested at Laboratory 2. Mean experimental yield force 412.8 N (SD 14.7 N); FEA ensemble mean 404.3 N. Percentage difference 2.06%, within acceptance bound. E/uval 0.58.",
      "comparedAgainst": "https://uofa.net/nagaraja/data/f1717-bench-lab2-n5",
      "prov:wasGeneratedBy": "https://uofa.net/nagaraja/activity/yield-force-analysis-lab2-run20240317"
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/nagaraja/vr/force-40mm-combined",
      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Force at 40 mm displacement — combined cohort (N=11), primary acceptance QoI",
      "description": "This result constitutes the primary acceptance criterion for COU1. Force at 40 mm displacement was evaluated across the full combined cohort of N=11 constructs spanning both laboratories. Laboratory 1 contributed six specimens tested on an MTS 858 Mini Bionix II servohydraulic frame at 25 mm/min crosshead speed following ASTM F1717-15 Section 8.3; Laboratory 2 contributed five specimens tested on an Instron 5967 dual-column frame at identical displacement rate. FEA ensemble predictions (three independent analyst teams using FDA-validated Abaqus 2021, Ansys Mechanical 2022R1, and DePuy Synthes in-house solver) were averaged prior to comparison. Mean experimental force at 40 mm: 638.2 N (pooled SD 22.9 N, CV 3.6%). FEA ensemble mean: 621.7 N. Absolute percentage difference: 2.59%, satisfying the pre-specified <10% acceptance bound. The validation uncertainty metric E/uval was computed as 0.72, below the 1.96 threshold, confirming no statistically significant bias. Sensitivity analyses confirmed that material property variability (titanium alloy Ti-6Al-4V lot-to-lot elastic modulus range ±3 GPa) contributed less than 0.8% to QoI spread. Contact interface friction coefficient (μ=0.22±0.04) contributed 1.1%. Mesh convergence had been established separately (see Discretization Error factor). The result is considered validated for the stated COU and acceptance bounds.",
      "comparedAgainst": "https://uofa.net/nagaraja/data/f1717-combined-n11"
    }
  ],
